title: Excel Sheet Column Number
content:
Given a column title as appear in an Excel sheet, return its corresponding column number.

For example:

    A -> 1
    B -> 2
    C -> 3
    ...
    Z -> 26
    AA -> 27
    AB -> 28 
    ...

Example 1:

Input: "A"
Output: 1

Example 2:

Input: "AB"
Output: 28

Example 3:

Input: "ZY"
Output: 701

 

Constraints:

  • 1 <= s.length <= 7
  • s consists only of uppercase English letters.
  • s is between "A" and "FXSHRXW".
